# ENTITY COMPONENT SYSTEM

## Design Pattern
Instead of class hierarchies (Enemy → BossEnemy → MegaBoss), use composition:
- Entity: Just an ID
- Components: Data containers
- Systems: Logic operators

## Implementation
```cpp
// Components are pure data
struct Position { float x, y; };
struct Health { int hp, maxHp; };
struct Sprite { std::string texId; int frame; };
struct Inventory { std::vector<Item> items; };

// Entity holds components
class Entity {
    uint32_t id;
    std::map<std::type_index, void*> components;
};

// Systems process entities
class MovementSystem {
    void update(float dt, std::vector<Entity>& entities) {
        for (auto& e : entities) {
            auto pos = e.getComponent<Position>();
            auto vel = e.getComponent<Velocity>();
            if (pos && vel) {
                pos->x += vel->vx * dt;
                pos->y += vel->vy * dt;
            }
        }
    }
};
```

## Benefits
- No deep inheritance chains
- Easy to add new behaviors (just add system)
- Data locality improves cache efficiency
- Reusable across player, enemies, NPCs

