# RENDERING & ANIMATION

## Layer System
Render in order:
1. Background (parallax layers)
2. Tiles/Terrain
3. Objects (doors, chests)
4. Enemies (sorted by Y for depth)
5. Player
6. Foreground (trees, buildings in front)
7. UI
8. Debug (collision boxes, AI paths)

## Animation States
```cpp
enum class AnimState { IDLE, WALK, RUN, JUMP, ATTACK, HURT, DEAD };

struct Animation {
    AnimState state;
    int currentFrame;
    float frameTimer;
    float frameDelay;
    int totalFrames;
    
    void update(float dt) {
        frameTimer += dt;
        if (frameTimer >= frameDelay) {
            currentFrame++;
            frameTimer = 0.0f;
            if (currentFrame >= totalFrames) {
                currentFrame = 0; // Or loop behavior
            }
        }
    }
};
```

## Spritesheet Layout
- All frames for one animation in a row
- Store frame width/height in data
